<!--
================================================================================
ui-extensions.md — minimal scaffold for a master/coordinator agent
================================================================================
This file activates an interactive tab on the host platform's dashboard.
Rename it from `ui-extensions.md.example` to `ui-extensions.md` to enable.
ONLY the team's master agent's copy is read; sub-agents are ignored.

Frontmatter:
  title:    Tab label in the host's navbar.
  requires: List of ${VAR} names that must resolve for the tab to be visible.
            (e.g. `[git_pat]` means a PAT must be configured before the tab
            appears.) See agents/UI_EXTENSIONS.md for the resolution order.
  apis:     Per-key API definitions. Each entry has `url`, `auth`, optional
            `headers`, and `refresh` (seconds). Both `url` and `auth` accept
            ${VAR} substitution; the proxy resolves these server-side.

Body tokens (use inside the markdown body):
  {{progress:open:closed[:label]}}              progress bar + stats line
  {{apitable:api_key:col1,col2,...[:Heading]}}  table with optional "Heading (N)"
  {{apilist:api_key:field[:Heading]}}           bullet list with optional "Heading (N)"

Auto-rendered when the API row has these fields:
  number       → `#NNN` prefix in muted monospace before the title
  html_url     → small ↗ link icon opening the row in a new tab
  open_issues + closed_issues → progress bar beneath the title cell (apitable)

The renderer is a skeleton. Markdown headings, paragraphs, lists, <hr>, and
the tokens above determine the entire visual flow — the host adds no card
wrap or chrome. See agents/UI_EXTENSIONS.md for the full spec.
================================================================================
-->

## Welcome

Edit this file to define your dashboard tab. Replace this content with
markdown plus the tokens listed above.
